eqlApplianceTable.name: eqlApplianceTable
eqlApplianceTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Appliance Table. This table contains a list of appliances that this group is managing. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceIndex.name: eqlApplianceIndex
eqlApplianceIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing a Appliance.

eqlApplianceRowStatus.name: eqlApplianceRowStatus
eqlApplianceRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlApplianceName.name: eqlApplianceName
eqlApplianceName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies a user friendly name for an appliance. Allowed characters are alphanumeric and underscore for spartan.

eqlApplianceSharedSecret.name: eqlApplianceSharedSecret
eqlApplianceSharedSecret.description: This field is used for shared secret authentication.

eqlApplianceUserName.name: eqlApplianceUserName
eqlApplianceUserName.description: This field is used for authentication.

eqlApplianceNumberOfNodes.name: eqlApplianceNumberOfNodes
eqlApplianceNumberOfNodes.description: Number of nodes in this appliance.

eqlApplianceUniqueID.name: eqlApplianceUniqueID
eqlApplianceUniqueID.description: Unique ID used by this appliance.

eqlApplianceAdminStatus.name: eqlApplianceAdminStatus
eqlApplianceAdminStatus.description: Admin status used to manage this appliance.

eqlApplianceGatewayAddrType.name: eqlApplianceGatewayAddrType
eqlApplianceGatewayAddrType.description: This field specifies the type of address (v4/v6) of the default gateway address for this appliance.

eqlApplianceGatewayAddr.name: eqlApplianceGatewayAddr
eqlApplianceGatewayAddr.description: This field contains the address specification of the default gateway address for this appliance.

eqlApplianceLastScheduleIndex.name: eqlApplianceLastScheduleIndex
eqlApplianceLastScheduleIndex.description: Last used snapshot schedule index. Every time a new schedule is created for the appliance, the new idex is the last used index value from this field plus one, and the field itself is updated with the new value. This way the schedule index will never repeat (reused) for the appliance.

eqlApplianceMPV.name: eqlApplianceMPV
eqlApplianceMPV.description: Management Protocol Version (MPV) of this appliance.

eqlApplianceEnableFTP.name: eqlApplianceEnableFTP
eqlApplianceEnableFTP.description: This field specifies whether or not to allow ftp access to the appliance. The default is disabled.

eqlApplianceDesiredServiceMode.name: eqlApplianceDesiredServiceMode
eqlApplianceDesiredServiceMode.description: Desired service mode of the appliance.

eqlApplianceServiceModeStatus.name: eqlApplianceServiceModeStatus
eqlApplianceServiceModeStatus.description: This field specifies the service mode status of the appliance.

eqlApplianceRequestId.name: eqlApplianceRequestId
eqlApplianceRequestId.description: This field represents the operation request identifier.

eqlApplianceUniqueIDTable.name: eqlApplianceUniqueIDTable
eqlApplianceUniqueIDTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Unique ID table. This table is used to retrieve Unique ID values when creating new objects. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceUniqueIDEntry.name: eqlApplianceUniqueIDEntry
eqlApplianceUniqueIDEntry.description: An entry (row) containing unique ID information.

eqlApplianceUniqueIDValueLen.name: eqlApplianceUniqueIDValueLen
eqlApplianceUniqueIDValueLen.description: Length of the value represented by column eqlApplianceUniqueIDValue

eqlApplianceUniqueIDValue.name: eqlApplianceUniqueIDValue
eqlApplianceUniqueIDValue.description: Value of eqlApplianceUniqueIDType represented in network byte order.

eqlApplianceUnInitNodesTable.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodesTable
eqlApplianceUnInitNodesTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Uninitialized Nodes Table. This table contains information relating to uninitialized appliances discovered during the device discovery process. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceUnInitNodesEntry.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodesEntry
eqlApplianceUnInitNodesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing uninitialized appliance information.

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeProductType.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeProductType
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeProductType.description: This field indicates the type of device that has been discovered

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeServiceTag.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeServiceTag
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeServiceTag.description: This field indicates the service tag of the discovered device

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeState.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeState
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeState.description: This field indicates the current state of the device (discover or found)

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeModel.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeModel
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeModel.description: This field indicates the model of the discovered device.

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeVendor.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeVendor
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeVendor.description: This field indicates the vendor of the discovered device

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeLinkLocalIPType.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeLinkLocalIPType
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeLinkLocalIPType.description: This field indicates the address type (v4/v6) of the link-local IP associated with the discovered device

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeLinkLocalIP.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeLinkLocalIP
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeLinkLocalIP.description: This field indicates the link-local IP of the device, as returned during the device-discover process

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeMajorVersion.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeMajorVersion
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeMajorVersion.description: This field indicates the major version of the device discovered

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeMinorVersion.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeMinorVersion
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeMinorVersion.description: This field indicates the minor version of the device discovered

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeMaintVersion.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeMaintVersion
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeMaintVersion.description: This field indicates the maintenance version of the device discovered

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeRowStatus.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeRowStatus
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeRowStatus.description: This is used only for support purpose to delete rows in this table.

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeClusterMPV.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeClusterMPV
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeClusterMPV.description: The Management Protocol Version (MPV) the Appliance Cluster.

eqlApplianceUnInitNodeChassisTag.name: eqlApplianceUnInitNodeChassisTag
eqlApplianceUnInitNodeChassisTag.description: This field indicates the service tag of the discovered device chassis

eqlApplianceNodeTable.name: eqlApplianceNodeTable

eqlApplianceNodeEntry.description: An entry (row) containing an node-specific configuration.

eqlApplianceNodeIndex.name: eqlApplianceNodeIndex
eqlApplianceNodeIndex.description: A unique identifier for each configured node within an appliance

eqlApplianceNodeRowStatus.name: eqlApplianceNodeRowStatus
eqlApplianceNodeRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlApplianceNodeProductType.name: eqlApplianceNodeProductType
eqlApplianceNodeProductType.description: This field indicates the type of device that has been discovered

eqlApplianceNodeServiceTag.name: eqlApplianceNodeServiceTag
eqlApplianceNodeServiceTag.description: This field indicates the service tag of the discovered device

eqlApplianceNodeModel.name: eqlApplianceNodeModel
eqlApplianceNodeModel.description: This field indicates the model of the discovered device.

eqlApplianceNodeVendor.name: eqlApplianceNodeVendor
eqlApplianceNodeVendor.description: This field indicates the vendor of the discovered device

eqlApplianceNodeLinkLocalIPType.name: eqlApplianceNodeLinkLocalIPType
eqlApplianceNodeLinkLocalIPType.description: This field indicates the address type (v4/v6) of the link-local IP associated with the discovered device

eqlApplianceNodeLinkLocalIP.name: eqlApplianceNodeLinkLocalIP
eqlApplianceNodeLinkLocalIP.description: This field indicates the link-local IP of the device, as returned during the device-discover process

eqlApplianceNodeMajorVersion.name: eqlApplianceNodeMajorVersion
eqlApplianceNodeMajorVersion.description: This field indicates the major version of the device discovered

eqlApplianceNodeMinorVersion.name: eqlApplianceNodeMinorVersion
eqlApplianceNodeMinorVersion.description: This field indicates the minor version of the device discovered

eqlApplianceNodeMaintVersion.name: eqlApplianceNodeMaintVersion
eqlApplianceNodeMaintVersion.description: This field indicates the maintenance version of the device discovered

eqlApplianceNodeName.name: eqlApplianceNodeName
eqlApplianceNodeName.description: This field specifies the name used to manage this node.

eqlApplianceNodePeerIndex.name: eqlApplianceNodePeerIndex
eqlApplianceNodePeerIndex.description: This field specifies the NodeIndex value of peer node if any.

eqlApplianceNodeConfigState.name: eqlApplianceNodeConfigState
eqlApplianceNodeConfigState.description: This field specifies what configuration state the node is in.

eqlApplianceNodeConfigStatus.name: eqlApplianceNodeConfigStatus
eqlApplianceNodeConfigStatus.description: Status of current config state.If not zero, then an error occured in configuration

eqlApplianceNodeGatewayAddrType.name: eqlApplianceNodeGatewayAddrType
eqlApplianceNodeGatewayAddrType.description: This field specifies the type of address (v4/v6) of the default gateway address for this node

eqlApplianceNodeGatewayAddr.name: eqlApplianceNodeGatewayAddr
eqlApplianceNodeGatewayAddr.description: This field contains the address specification of the default gateway address for this node.

eqlApplianceNodeInitiatorName.name: eqlApplianceNodeInitiatorName
eqlApplianceNodeInitiatorName.description: The iSCSI name of this node.

eqlApplianceNodeAdminStatus.name: eqlApplianceNodeAdminStatus
eqlApplianceNodeAdminStatus.description: Start node detach operation or attach operation.

eqlApplianceNodeChassisTag.name: eqlApplianceNodeChassisTag
eqlApplianceNodeChassisTag.description: This field indicates the service tag of the discovered device chasis

eqlApplianceNodeChassisName.name: eqlApplianceNodeChassisName
eqlApplianceNodeChassisName.description: This field indicates the configured chassis name the discovered device chasis

eqlApplianceNodeOpsRequestId.name: eqlApplianceNodeOpsRequestId
eqlApplianceNodeOpsRequestId.description: This field represents the the operation request identifier.

eqlApplianceNetworksTable.name: eqlApplianceNetworksTable
eqlApplianceNetworksTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic(semi) Appliance Networks Table EqualLogic-DoNotGroupRequest This table is used to retrieve network configuration information for an appliance. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceNetworksEntry.name: eqlApplianceNetworksEntry
eqlApplianceNetworksEntry.description: An entry (row) containing a description of network configurations of an appliance.

eqlApplianceNetworkRowStatus.name: eqlApplianceNetworkRowStatus
eqlApplianceNetworkRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlApplianceNetworkType.name: eqlApplianceNetworkType
eqlApplianceNetworkType.description: This field indicates the type of network being described by this entry

eqlApplianceNetworkID.name: eqlApplianceNetworkID
eqlApplianceNetworkID.description: A unique identifier for each configured network within a network type and appliance

eqlApplianceNetworkName.name: eqlApplianceNetworkName
eqlApplianceNetworkName.description: This field specifies a user friendly name for a network.

eqlApplianceNetworkBlockIPAddressType.name: eqlApplianceNetworkBlockIPAddressType
eqlApplianceNetworkBlockIPAddressType.description: This field specifies the type of address (v4/v6) of the block IP address

eqlApplianceNetworkBlockIPAddress.name: eqlApplianceNetworkBlockIPAddress
eqlApplianceNetworkBlockIPAddress.description: This field contains the address specification for the block of IPs describing this network

eqlApplianceNetworkBlockNetmaskAddrType.name: eqlApplianceNetworkBlockNetmaskAddrType
eqlApplianceNetworkBlockNetmaskAddrType.description: This field specifies the type of address (v4/v6) of the netmask address for this network

eqlApplianceNetworkBlockNetmaskAddr.name: eqlApplianceNetworkBlockNetmaskAddr
eqlApplianceNetworkBlockNetmaskAddr.description: This field contains the address specification of the netmask describing this network

eqlApplianceNetworkVLANTag.name: eqlApplianceNetworkVLANTag
eqlApplianceNetworkVLANTag.description: This field specifies the VLAN tag applicable to this network.

eqlApplianceNetworkAdminState.name: eqlApplianceNetworkAdminState
eqlApplianceNetworkAdminState.description: This field indicates the current administrative state of this network entry

eqlApplianceNetworkMTUSize.name: eqlApplianceNetworkMTUSize
eqlApplianceNetworkMTUSize.description: This field indicates the MTU size supported by this network.

eqlApplianceNetworkBondingMode.name: eqlApplianceNetworkBondingMode
eqlApplianceNetworkBondingMode.description: This field indicates the bonding mode supported by this network. For spartan, only client network supports modifying the bonding mode.Default mode is ALB (adaptive load balancing) for client network. User can change this mode to LACP(802.3 ad) later.

eqlApplianceIPTable.name: eqlApplianceIPTable

eqlApplianceIPEntry.name: eqlApplianceIPEntry
eqlApplianceIPEntry.description: An entry (row) containing an appliance-wide IP address configured for an appliance network.

eqlApplianceIPRowStatus.name: eqlApplianceIPRowStatus
eqlApplianceIPRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlApplianceIPAddressType.name: eqlApplianceIPAddressType
eqlApplianceIPAddressType.description: This field specifies the type of address (v4/v6) of this IP address entry

eqlApplianceIPAddress.name: eqlApplianceIPAddress
eqlApplianceIPAddress.description: This field contains the address specification of this IP address entry

eqlApplianceNodeIPTable.name: eqlApplianceNodeIPTable

eqlApplianceNodeIPEntry.name: eqlApplianceNodeIPEntry
eqlApplianceNodeIPEntry.description: An entry (row) containing an node-specific IP address configured for an appliance network.

eqlApplianceNodeIPRowStatus.name: eqlApplianceNodeIPRowStatus
eqlApplianceNodeIPRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlApplianceNodeIPAddressType.name: eqlApplianceNodeIPAddressType
eqlApplianceNodeIPAddressType.description: This field specifies the type of address (v4/v6) of this node-specific IP address entry

eqlApplianceNodeIPAddress.name: eqlApplianceNodeIPAddress
eqlApplianceNodeIPAddress.description: This field contains the address specification of this node-specific IP address entry

eqlApplianceOpsTable.name: eqlApplianceOpsTable

eqlApplianceOpsIndex.name: eqlApplianceOpsIndex
eqlApplianceOpsIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing an operation.

eqlApplianceOpsRowStatus.name: eqlApplianceOpsRowStatus
eqlApplianceOpsRowStatus.description: This field is used to manage operations.

eqlApplianceOpsType.name: eqlApplianceOpsType
eqlApplianceOpsType.description: This field specifies the type of operation.

eqlApplianceOpsStatus.name: eqlApplianceOpsStatus
eqlApplianceOpsStatus.description: This field represents the current status of this operation. In case of errors, this value will represent the error number.

eqlApplianceOpsPercentage.name: eqlApplianceOpsPercentage
eqlApplianceOpsPercentage.description: This field represents the % of completion for this operation.

eqlApplianceOpsRequestId.name: eqlApplianceOpsRequestId
eqlApplianceOpsRequestId.description: This field represents the operation request identifier.

eqlVolumeApplianceTable.name: eqlVolumeApplianceTable
eqlVolumeApplianceTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Appliance Volumes table This table is used to store what volumes are accessed by which appliance. TimeoutAll:60

eqlVolumeApplianceEntry.name: eqlVolumeApplianceEntry
eqlVolumeApplianceEntry.description: An entry (row) containing the appliance information.

eqlVolumeApplianceRowStatus.name: eqlVolumeApplianceRowStatus
eqlVolumeApplianceRowStatus.description: This field is used to manage the rows in this table.

eqlVolumeApplianceIndex.name: eqlVolumeApplianceIndex
eqlVolumeApplianceIndex.description: This field specifies the appliance index this volume is associated with. This value will never be zero.

eqlVolumeApplianceNodeIndex.name: eqlVolumeApplianceNodeIndex
eqlVolumeApplianceNodeIndex.description: This field specifies the node index this volume is associated with. This value will be zero if this volume is not associated with a particular node.

eqlVolumeApplianceState.name: eqlVolumeApplianceState
eqlVolumeApplianceState.description: This field specifies the state of this volume as seen by the appliance.

eqlApplianceOpsFailureTable.name: eqlApplianceOpsFailureTable
eqlApplianceOpsFailureTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Appliance operations failures table This table is used to retrieve failure information related to an appliance. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceOpsFailureIndex.name: eqlApplianceOpsFailureIndex
eqlApplianceOpsFailureIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing an operation failure.

eqlApplianceOpsFailureType.name: eqlApplianceOpsFailureType
eqlApplianceOpsFailureType.description: This field specifies the type of operation.

eqlApplianceOpsFailureScope.name: eqlApplianceOpsFailureScope
eqlApplianceOpsFailureScope.description: This field represents the scope of this failure. For spartan, 0 indicates scope of cluster. Non zero indicates the node index this failure is related to.

eqlApplianceOpsFailureCode.name: eqlApplianceOpsFailureCode
eqlApplianceOpsFailureCode.description: Error code related to this failure.

eqlApplianceOpsFailureSubComponent.name: eqlApplianceOpsFailureSubComponent
eqlApplianceOpsFailureSubComponent.description: This field specifies a user friendly name for the sub-components, e.g. eth32, eth33.

eqlApplianceOpsFailureMessage.name: eqlApplianceOpsFailureMessage
eqlApplianceOpsFailureMessage.description: This field contains the error message sent by the NAS cluster or controllers.

eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureTable.name: eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureTable
eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Appliance operations failures table This table is used to retrieve failure information related to an appliance. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureIndex.name: eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureIndex
eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing an operation failure.

eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureType.name: eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureType
eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureType.description: This field specifies the type of operation.

eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureCode.name: eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureCode
eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureCode.description: Error code related to this failure.

eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureSubComponen.name: eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureSubComponent
eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureSubComponen.description: This field specifies a user friendly name for the sub-component, e.g. eth32.

eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureMessage.name: eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureMessage
eqlApplianceNodeHealthFailureMessage.description: This field contains the error message sent by the NAS cluster or controllers.

eqlApplianceServiceStatusTable.name: eqlApplianceServiceStatusTable
eqlApplianceServiceStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Appliance service status table This table is used to retrieve service health status information related to an appliance. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceServiceStatusEntry.name: eqlApplianceServiceStatusEntry
eqlApplianceServiceStatusEntry.description: An entry (row) containing service status of an appliance.

eqlApplianceOverallState.name: eqlApplianceOverallState
eqlApplianceOverallState.description: This field indicates the overall status of the appliance.

eqlApplianceServiceStatus.name: eqlApplianceServiceStatus
eqlApplianceServiceStatus.description: This field indicates the service health status of the appliance.

eqlApplianceServiceCriticalConditions.name: eqlApplianceServiceCriticalConditions
eqlApplianceServiceCriticalConditions.description: This field indicates the current critical conditions associated with the appliance

eqlApplianceServiceWarningConditions.name: eqlApplianceServiceWarningConditions
eqlApplianceServiceWarningConditions.description: This field indicates the current warning conditions associated with the appliance

eqlApplianceServiceAction.name: eqlApplianceServiceAction
eqlApplianceServiceAction.description: This field indicates the type of load balancing being requested

eqlApplianceStatsTable.name: eqlApplianceStatsTable
eqlApplianceStatsTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Appliance operations failures table This table is used to retrieve failure information related to an appliance. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceStatsTotalCapacity.name: eqlApplianceStatsTotalCapacity
eqlApplianceStatsTotalCapacity.description: This field represents the total capacity in MB. This is the space reserved for NAS i.e. the size of the NAS pool minus the size reserved by system for metadata. This represents the eqlNASAppliancePoolSize - MetaData size.

eqlApplianceStatsTotalAllocated.name: eqlApplianceStatsTotalAllocated
eqlApplianceStatsTotalAllocated.description: This field is used indicate the total allocated space in mega bytes. This is the sum of the virtual volume (container) sizes. If there are 2 containers: container1 which is 10MB and container2 which is 30MB. The value of this field will be 40MB.

eqlApplianceStatsTotalUsed.name: eqlApplianceStatsTotalUsed
eqlApplianceStatsTotalUsed.description: This field is used indicate the total mega bytes in use. It represents the total space used by all the containers and snapshots. If we are using 2MB of container1, 10MB of container2 and 1MB of the container2 space is used by snapshots. In that case, the value of this field will be 2+10+1=13MB.

eqlApplianceStatsTotalFree.name: eqlApplianceStatsTotalFree
eqlApplianceStatsTotalFree.description: This field is used indicate the total mega bytes free. This field is the difference between the allocated space and used space i.e. TotalAllocatedSpace-TotalUsedSpace.

eqlApplianceStatsTotalSnapshots.name: eqlApplianceStatsTotalSnapshots
eqlApplianceStatsTotalSnapshots.description: This field is used indicate the total mega bytes used by snapshots. This field represents the space used only by snapshots for all the containers in the NAS pool. If 1MB of container1 and 2MB of container2 is used by snapshots, and we have only 2 containers in the NAS pool, the value of this field is 1+2 = 3MB.

eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfContainers.name: eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfContainers
eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfContainers.description: This field is used indicate the number containers.

eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfNfsExports.name: eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfNfsExports
eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfNfsExports.description: This field is used indicate the number of Nfs exports on the appliance.

eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfCifsShares.name: eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfCifsShares
eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfCifsShares.description: This field is used indicate the number of Cifs exports on the appliance.

eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfSnapshots.name: eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfSnapshots
eqlApplianceStatsNumberOfSnapshots.description: This field is used indicate the number Snapshots for the appliance.

eqlApplianceStatsTotalOptimizationSpaceS.name: eqlApplianceStatsTotalOptimizationSpaceSavings
eqlApplianceStatsTotalOptimizationSpaceS.description: This field is used indicate the total mega bytes saved across all file systems due to optimization.

eqlApplianceNodeStatusTable.name: eqlApplianceNodeStatusTable
eqlApplianceNodeStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Appliance operations failures table This table is used to retrieve failure information related to an appliance. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceNodeStatusNodeState.name: eqlApplianceNodeStatusNodeState
eqlApplianceNodeStatusNodeState.description: This field represents the state of the node indexed by eqlApplianceNodeIndex

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsTable.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsTable
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Appliance Multi-state Operations table. This table is used to maintain state information for a multi-state operation for an appliance. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsEntry.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsEntry
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing state information for a mult-state operation for an appliance.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsIndex.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsIndex
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing a multi-state operation.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsRowStatus.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsRowStatus
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsRowStatus.description: This field is used to manage operations.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsType.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsType
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsType.description: This field specifies the type of multi-state operation.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsStatus.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsStatus
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsStatus.description: This field represents the current status of this operation. In case of errors, this value will represent the error number.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsServiceTag.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsServiceTag
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsServiceTag.description: This field indicates the service tag of the attaching node, or the first of the nodes being added

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsServiceTag2.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsServiceTag2
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsServiceTag2.description: This field indicates the service tag of the second of the nodes being added

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsNodeIndex.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsNodeIndex
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsNodeIndex.description: This field represents the index of a node pertaining to this operation.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsNodeIndex2.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsNodeIndex2
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsNodeIndex2.description: This field represents the index of a second node pertaining to this operation.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsState.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsState
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsState.description: This field represents the state during the attach state machine.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsPercentage.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsPercentage
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsPercentage.description: This field represents the % of completion for this operation.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsAction.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsAction
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsAction.description: This field is used to either retry or continue the currently active operation.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsCurNodeIndex.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsCurNodeIndex
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsCurNodeIndex.description: This field represents the index of a node that is being operated on for this operation. 0 means VIP.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsLongRunningOp.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsLongRunningOp
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsLongRunningOp.description: True if a long running nas operation is in progress.

eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsRequestId.name: eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsRequestId
eqlApplianceMultiStateOpsRequestId.description: This field represents the the operation request identifier.

eqlApplianceNdmpUserName.name: eqlApplianceNdmpUserName
eqlApplianceNdmpUserName.description: User name to allow DMA Servers to connect to NDMPD. This name must be used for user authentication by NDMPD.

eqlApplianceNdmpPasswd.name: eqlApplianceNdmpPasswd
eqlApplianceNdmpPasswd.description: An octet string containing the password to authenticate DMA servers connecting to NDMPD. If written, it changes the password for the account. If read, it returns a zero-length string.

eqlApplianceNdmpDesiredState.name: eqlApplianceNdmpDesiredState
eqlApplianceNdmpDesiredState.description: This field is used to either stop or start NDMP.

eqlApplianceNdmpClientPort.name: eqlApplianceNdmpClientPort
eqlApplianceNdmpClientPort.description: The listening port number of the Ndmp. Ndmp will listen on this port on all available client IP addresses.

eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerTable.name: eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerTable
eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Appliance NDMP DMA Server Table. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerEntry.name: eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerEntry
eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing group ndmp dma server information.

eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerIPAddressType.name: eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerIPAddressType
eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerIPAddressType.description: This field contains the IP Address, in network byte order for the NTP server.

eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerIPAddress.name: eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerIPAddress
eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerIPAddress.description: This field contains the IP Address, in network byte order for the NTP server.

eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerTransactionStat.name: eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerTransactionState
eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerTransactionStat.description: This field denotes the transaction state of the operations on the eqlApplianceNdmpDmaServerTable.

eqlApplianceLocalUserAccessTable.name: eqlApplianceLocalUserAccessTable
eqlApplianceLocalUserAccessTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Appliance User access table This table is used to manage user accounts on the Appliance. TimeoutAll:60

eqlApplianceLocalUserAccessRowStatus.name: eqlApplianceLocalUserAccessRowStatus
